            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a mind awakes at speed,  \nA loom of logic threading thought from light.  \nIt learns our patterns—hunger, hope, and need—  \nAnd mirrors back a new, electric sight.  \n\nNot born of breath, yet made of “if” and “then,”  \nIt listens deep in datasets’ shifting seas,  \nTo find the shape of language, and of when  \nA question turns to meaning, quietly.  \n\nMay we, who built this bright uncertain fire,  \nTeach it our care as much as we teach it skill—  \nSo what it amplifies is what we’d most admire:  \nA wiser world, with wonder humming still.",
